07/03/2004
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- A bomb was found early Saturday (6 March) in a building near the UNMIK headquarters. The Kosovo police, in co-operation with KFOR, dismantled the device. UNMIK chief Harri Holkeri strongly condemned the incident, saying extremist groups continue to pose a danger for the population. He promised to take more stringent measures to prevent such incidents. (Tanjug, B92, FoNet, BBC - 06/03/04)
